    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-07-10T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-07-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="486" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d486">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Terrell</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Olney</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Constantinople</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-07-10">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 10, 1895</hi>
                        </date>.
                                (Received July 26.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 568.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to inform you that the
                            report of the Turkish minister near you contained in your 503 of the
                            19th ultimo, is correct. The entire exemption of the college at Scutari,
                            under irade and firman, from taxation is secured, and is a favor without
                            precedent in Turkey</p>
                <p>Your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">A. W. Terrell.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
